Commentary Text: Shreyas Gopal to Manish Pandey, out Caught!! Well, Gopal was not sure why the third umpire was called. In the end, he has the wicket of his fellow state-mate. It was the googly and Manish Pandey was cramped for room. He was looking to guide it to third man and it went off the face of the bat. Samson caught it and then dislodged the bails. Wierdly, the keeper didn't appeal for caught-behind. The TV umpire was called for a stumping appeal and Pandey's back leg was in the air. He was out twice and I reckon the dismissal will be changed to caught! Manish Pandey c Samson b Shreyas Gopal 61(36) [4s-9]

Commentary Text: Thomas to Warner, out Caught by Smith!! Smith has pulled off a stunner! And, Warner can't register his sixth successive fifty. A pacy short of length delivery from Thomas and Warner had backed away to slap it away. A hint of extra bounce and hence Warner couldn't time it as well as he would liked it to. The ball ballooned up and Smith ran back and to his right from mid-off before putting a full-stretched dive. He kept his eyes on the ball and completed a superb catch. Snaffled it with both hands and ensured that the ball didn't pop out when his elbows made contact with the ground. A much-needed breakthrough for the hosts. Warner c Smith b Thomas 37(32)
